FY 2025 Plans: Develop artificial intelligence (AI) / Machine Learning (ML) algorithms for classification of naval
acoustic signatures using software tools and acoustic buoys.

Automate the current manual acoustic classification processes, which are manpower intensive and slow,
into an automated process that reduces errors in classifying passive acoustic signal energy from operational
environments.

Develop data labeling solutions that enable labeling for machine learning across multiple sensor types.

Develop prototype software tools to do the timely, accurate, and precise labeling of passive acoustic energy,
with the goal of early warning and detection, tracking, and classification of adversarial manned and unmanned
surface and subsurface maritime acoustic signatures.

Deploy prototype tools to commercial air, surface, and subsurface test ranges for test and evaluation and to
provide simulation data similar to the U.S. Navy operational environments.

Develop, integrate, and deliver a prototype portable modular buoy system that provides near real time Bearing
Time Records (BTRs) and spectrograms to collect acoustic data for commercial software developers to power
the design and deployment of advanced AI algorithms for undersea battlespace awareness.
