Description: The objective of this activity is to capitalize technology breakthroughs of Government and Industry
to develop and integrate components, including subsystems, into prototypes quickly, mature into products,
and provide to the warfighter for demonstration, test, analysis, Fleet/Force exercises, and/or tests in simulated
or actual environments. NavalX, partnering with Fleet/Force warfighting commands for demonstrations,
iterates throughout the innovation process to achieve optimal warfighter results. The net results are early
warfighter feedback, assessment of CONOPS, analysis of mission impact, and an understanding of DOTMLPF
considerations to mature and transition technology solutions.

NavalX participates in live exercises and demonstration events such as Integrated Battle Problem, Silent Swarm,
Trident Spectre, Hybrid Fleet, and others to analyze and assess industry technology candidates. NavalX also
leverages these events as demonstration and test opportunities for technology prototypes to assess their overall
mission effectiveness and receive warfighter feedback on human factors, safety, usability, and interoperability,
and other critical success metrics.

FY 2025 Plans:
- Manage an NRE experimentation plan which will guide multi-year technology development efforts in response
to emerging concepts and doctrine. Leverage experimentation as an excursion to traditional programs to
address additional warfighter needs and/or mitigate capability delivery risk.

- Continue to maintain and leverage innovation experimentation opportunities to guide prioritized concept
investigations and iterations in support of fleet/force needs and strategic technology development initiatives.

- Continue Fleet engagement and experimentation plan for technology assessments, including Integrated Battle
Problem 25, UNITAS, COMPACFLT PACIFIC DRAGON, and others. Conduct tech scans, tech assessments,
and follow-up technology transition engagements.

- Continue to develop and manage AI technologies for the NRE AI ecosystem.




