Description: This project includes the technology transition initiatives which solve mission focused, human
centered challenges using innovation and design thinking methods. Technology initiatives tailor the analysis,
development, and solution generation methods to the respective topic and scope.

FY 2025 Plans:
- Continue projects that solve mission focused, human-centered challenges using innovation and systems
engineering methods for the Navy and United States Marine Corps (USMC) by providing initial kickstarter
investment to analysis, development, and transition new technologies through the innovation operations
cycle. NavalX will support discovery of trends, sharing lessons learned, and empowering the workforce to
solve problems and build their agility skills by providing high-quality, low friction training and support to equip
commands with warfighter centered fundamentals.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
- Identify, prioritize, and analyze technologies to solve mission focused, human-centered challenges using
innovation and systems engineering methods for the Navy and United States Marine Corps (USMC) by providing
analysis, facilitating development, and managing the transition of new technologies through the innovation
operations cycle.

- Initiate the Technology Analysis process using capability readiness assessments, business and acquisition
readiness, and the mission benefit and warfighter utility assessments to prioritize and select commercial and
dual-use technology for incubation and rapid transition.

- Provide the analysis to support 10 technology scans, driven by validated Fleet/Force problem statements
traceable to IPLs or other urgent needs statements, leveraging the NavalX Salesforce System (NXSS) database
of technology leads and potential solutions. Provide the analysis to support 1 prize challenge executed across
the ecosystem by the Tech Bridges.
