and affordable capabilities for the Soldier Providing Soldiers with the technology supporting the Army of 2040. Supports
Aviation, Network, Ground, Soldier, Basic Research, Medical, Weapons, and Sensing & Intel Portfolio Directors, responding to
scientific, technical and programmatic challenges. Supports Independent Review Team analysis of technology maturity as part
of Technology Area Readiness Assessments. Serves as Office of the Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Army, Research and
Technology (DASA(R&T)) central point of contact for S&T Metrics, Army S&T strategy development, Strategic Portfolio Analysis
Review, evaluation of technical risks, earned value assessment, and technical and financial health of S&T projects.

