Title: Interoperability Certification and Assessment                                                                       12.463      14.083      14.154      0.000      14.154
                                                                                                           Articles:           -           -           -          -           -
Description: Description: This SFI pillar provides: interoperability assessments via the Distributed Integration
& Interoperability Assessment Capability (DIIAC), the technical assessment of interoperable systems to meet
mission requirements, Strike Group Interoperability Capabilities and Limitations (SGI C&L), and Tactical
Information Coordinator Technical Aid (TIC TECHAID) updates. Strike Force Interoperability certification
and assessments inform NAVSEA/PEOs the extent of interoperable warfare systems at the platform and
Strike Group levels, as well as new systems and platforms under development. The DIIAC provides the only
opportunity for comprehensive interoperability testing of combat system and C5I configuration items prior
to shipboard delivery for operational use in surface combatant platforms and Strike Groups. The DIIAC is
comprised of 23 land-based test sites from multiple Navy bases connected via classified network, and provides
operational configurations for all naval combat systems. SFI funds the full interoperability characterization testing
to include the requisite warfare system interoperability analysis and risk assessments needed to support the
Warfare Systems Certification Decision (WSCD). SFI can support the warfare system's acquisition community
by testing their developmental items for interoperability using the DIIAC. However, it is the cognizant acquisition
program's responsibility to fund subsequent data analysis and risk assessment. The DIIAC infrastructure is
available, but not funded, to support the surface Navy's participation in the Joint Testing Environments as well as
the Maritime Theater Missile Defense (MTMD) Coalition Forces interoperability testing.

SFI maintains and updates the Strike Group Interoperability Capabilities & Limitations (SGI C&L) database
to accurately reflect the "state of the TDL/COP" (tactical data links/common operational picture) in every
operational theater. SGI C&Ls for all Strike Groups, Independent Deployers, and (when funded) the applicable
Coalition and Joint partners, are maintained on a secure internet protocol routing network (SIPRNET) website for
operational forces, trainers and the technical community. SGI C&L addresses known strike group compositions
and provides a fleet modifiable force SGI C&L "tool" that allows users to generate SGI C&L documents for their

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                               FY 2026   FY 2026      FY 2026
                                                                                                                          FY 2024   FY 2025    Base      OOC          Total
specific force compositions. The TIC TECHAID is a single, cohesive set of operation checklists for the sailor that
supports current operational use of these systems to meet tactical Information Exchange Requirements (IERs).
TIC TECHAIDS are prepared for deploying Carrier Strike Groups (CSG's), Amphibious Ready Group (ARG's)
and Independent Deployers. SGI C&L and TIC TECHAIDS readily inform Fleet operators and warfighters of the
acquisition community's efforts to improve C5I capabilities and any interoperability issues or limitations that exist.

