B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                 FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
The Airframe Enhancements for Launched Effects Development will align with Congressional Intent and current Utility Helicopter
Project Office (UHPO) requirements by focusing on the sensitivity analysis and design. This analysis will evaluate the overall
design space for aircraft changes that will optimize aircraft Design Gross Weight (DGW) around future growth provisions,
including envisioned technology insertion and Launched Effects (LE). This funding will continue to push the design efforts
closer to Preliminary Design Review (PDR) and Critical Design Review (CDR) for the H-60M platform. The airframe structural
enhancements effort is being accomplished in conjunction with the digital backbone in support of H-60 modernization and includes
a sensitivity analysis to understand key drivers for modernization capabilities and integration with legacy components within the
aircraft.
FY 2027 Plans:
The Airframe Enhancements for Launched Effects Development will align with Congressional Intent and current Utility Helicopter
Project Office (UHPO) requirements by focusing on the sensitivity analysis and design. This analysis will evaluate the overall
design space for aircraft changes that will optimize aircraft Design Gross Weight (DGW) around future growth provisions,
including envisioned technology insertion and Launched Effects (LE). This funding will continue to push the design efforts
closer to Preliminary Design Review (PDR) and Critical Design Review (CDR) for the H-60M platform. The airframe structural
enhancements effort is being accomplished in conjunction with the digital backbone in support of H-60 modernization and includes
a sensitivity analysis to understand key drivers for modernization capabilities and integration with legacy components within the
aircraft.
