The Engineering and Manufacturing Development (EMD) phase produced three production representative test articles to support a Production Decision. This phase
includes contractor and government led ground and flight system level qualification testing which requires completion of a variety of component and system level testing
such as Electromagnetic Environmental Effects (E3), and aircraft subsystem Live-Fire Test and Evaluation (LFTE). This testing will result in airworthiness qualification
and culminate with an Operational Demonstration and Material Release (MR). Following the Operational Demonstration recurring test requirements include qualification
of obsolescence driven updates, and software flight testing and electronic warfare testing.

