       Change Summary Explanation
       Cost:
       2069: FY26 funding decrease of $2.727M due to development efforts transitioning to sustainment efforts (PE 0204136N, BLI 0515) as IRST Full Rate Production
       Decision Review (FRPDR) is Q3FY25.
       9999: Not Applicable

       Technical:
       2069: Not Applicable
       9999: Not Applicable

       Schedule:
       2069:
       Systems Development:
       Block II, Phase II hardware/software end date shifted from 2QFY24 to 2QFY25 due to delays in completion of component qualification testing and subsequent
       generation of reports. Qualification test assets had to be diverted to support Operational Test (OT) events due to hardware production rate challenges resulting
       in asset availability constraints. Qual Test/Maturity and IRST Agile Software Delivery end date also shifted from 2QFY24 to 3QFY24 due to delays in completion
       of component qualification testing and the need to divert test assets for Operational Test (OT) events. Sensor hardware/software improvements will begin one
       quarter earlier than planned (3QFY24 vice 4QFY24) due to implementation of Agile software development allowing for more efficient software development cycle
       times.

       Test & Evaluation:
       IOT&E previously planned for 1QFY24-3QFY24 has shifted to 2QFY24-1QFY25 due to additional time taken during Developmental Test (DT) to demonstrate that
       pod and aircraft software were stable enough to enter into Operational Test (OT) as well as the timeline required for OT to complete their required test events,
       and Verification of Correction of Deficiency (VCD) previously planned to begin 2QFY24 will now begin 2QFY25 due to the updated timeline required to complete
       OT, establish Initial Operational Capability (IOC) in 1QFY25 and conduct a Full Rate Production Decision Review (FRPDR) in 3QFY25. Initial squadron standup
       will happen at this time and VCD efforts can commence, and end in 4QFY25, as the program transitions to sustainment.

       Production Milestones:
       LRIP 5 delivery previously planned for 2QFY24 has moved to 2QFY25 due to production delivery delays experienced to date in LRIP III. While fixes have been
       implemented to address the root cause of those delays, there is limited opportunity to recover schedule. This has shifted each LRIP and FRP delivery thereafter
       by two quarters.

       9999:
       - Not Applicable

